## ✨ Feature Reference

### 1. 🖼️ Image Upload (`ImageUpload.svelte`)
| How | Details |
|-----|---------|
| Click to browse | Opens file picker |
| Drag & drop | Drop images directly onto the upload zone |
| Supported formats | PNG, JPG, GIF, WebP |
| Auto-fit | Oversized images are automatically scaled to fit 80% of the A4 canvas |
| Auto-center | Each new image is placed in the center of the canvas, offset by 20px per image to avoid full overlap |

---

### 2. 🖱️ Drag & Move (Canvas)
- **Click + drag** any image to move it freely on the canvas.
- Movement is **unbounded** – you can push images off-canvas while dragging; they snap back to the edge on release (elastic clamping).
- Dragging starts after the pointer moves **>3px**, so a click doesn't accidentally move an image.
- **Pointer capture** is used so dragging continues even if the mouse briefly leaves the image.

---

### 3. 📐 Resize (`ImageItem.svelte`)
- Four corner handles (**NW, NE, SW, SE**) appear when an image is selected.
- **Default**: Aspect-ratio locked resize (drag corner = proportional scaling).
- **Hold Shift**: Free resize — width and height can be changed independently.
- Side handles (**N, S, E, W**) also maintain aspect ratio by adjusting the opposite dimension proportionally.
- Minimum size enforced: **20×20px**.

---

### 4. 🔄 Rotation (`ImageItem.svelte`)
| Action | Result |
|--------|--------|
| **Rotation handle** (circle above image) | Free rotation — drag to any angle |
| **Rotate button** (sidebar panel) | Snaps 90° clockwise each click |

The rotation handle appears at the top-center of a selected image as a cyan circle on a short stem.

---

### 5. ✂️ Crop (`CropModal.svelte`)
Clicking the **Crop icon** on the selection toolbar opens a fullscreen crop modal.

**Inside the crop modal:**
| Feature | How to Use |
|---------|------------|
| **Pan image** | Click + drag the image behind the crop box |
| **Zoom image** | Mouse wheel, or use +/- buttons |
| **Move crop box** | Click + drag inside the cyan crop box |
| **Resize crop box** | Drag the 4 corner handles of the crop box |
| **Rule-of-thirds grid** | Displayed inside the crop box automatically |
| **Aspect ratio presets** | Buttons: **Free**, **1:1**, **4:3**, **16:9** |
| **Apply** | Click "Apply Crop" to confirm; replaces the image's source URL |
| **Cancel / Escape** | Close without changing anything |

Crops are **non-destructive** in the sense that the original image URL is still stored for future re-crop reference.

---

### 6. 💬 Text Overlays (`ImageItem.svelte`)
Three types of text overlays are available via the selection side-panel:

| Button | Label | Behavior |
|--------|-------|----------|
| `T` icon | **Inner text** | Semi-transparent bar at the **bottom inside** the image |
| `TOP` | **Outer top text** | Bar placed **above** the image |
| `BOT` | **Outer bottom text** | Bar placed **below** the image |

**Text features:**
- Editable textarea — just click and type.
- **Auto-resize**: The text box grows vertically as you type.
- **Font size**: Drag the resize handle (thin bar at the top of the text area) up or down to change font size (range: 10–200px).
- **Remove**: Hover over the text area to see a red ✕ button in the corner.
- All text is rendered into the export (PNG/PDF) with proper word wrapping.

---

### 7. 🎨 Image Filters (`ImageFilters.svelte`)
The filter panel appears in the **left sidebar** when an image is selected.

| Filter | Type | Range |
|--------|------|-------|
| **Negative** | Toggle | On / Off |
| **Grayscale** | Toggle | On / Off |
| **Brightness** | Slider | 0% – 200% (default 100%) |
| **Contrast** | Slider | 0% – 200% (default 100%) |
| **Saturation** | Slider | 0% – 200% (default 100%) |

- All filters apply in real-time using CSS `filter`.
- **Reset** button (↺ icon) resets all filters to defaults.
- Filters are preserved when exported to PNG/PDF.

---

### 8. 📄 Multi-Page Support (`+page.svelte`)
Image Arranger supports multiple A4 pages in a single session.

| Control | Location | Action |
|---------|----------|--------|
| `‹` `›` arrows | Header | Navigate previous/next page |
| Page input box | Header | Type a page number + Enter to jump |
| `+` button | Header | Add a new blank page after the current page |
| `🗑️ Delete` button | Header | Delete the current page (clears images if it's the last page) |

- Each page holds its own independent set of images.
- Images are scoped to their page — switching pages deselects the current image.
- **PDF export** renders all pages as separate PDF pages in one file.
- **PNG export** is single-page only (disabled if you have more than 1 page).

---

### 9. 🔍 Canvas Zoom (`+page.svelte`)
- A **slider in the header** controls the canvas zoom.
- Range: **25% – 200%** of actual A4 size.
- The current zoom percentage is displayed next to the slider.
- Zoom only affects the editing view — exports are always at full A4 resolution.

---

### 10. 📤 Export (`exportUtils.js`)
| Format | Button | Details |
|--------|--------|---------|
| **PNG** | Blue gradient button | Single-page only; 2× resolution (1588px wide); transparent supported |
| **PDF** | Purple gradient button | Multi-page; each page is JPEG-compressed inside the PDF at A4 size |

- Export renders a fresh off-screen `<canvas>` at **2× scale** for sharpness (not a screenshot).
- All transforms (position, scale, rotation), filters, and text overlays are faithfully re-rendered.
- File is automatically named with a timestamp, e.g. `image-arrangement-2026-03-26T15-30-00.pdf`.

> **Note**: JPG export is implemented in code (`exportAsJPEG`) but not currently wired to a button in the UI.

---

### 11. 🗑️ Delete & Clear
| Action | How |
|--------|-----|
| Delete one image | Select image → click **🗑️** in the side panel |
| Clear all images on page | Click the **🗑️** icon in the image list header |
| Delete the whole page | Click the **Delete** page button in the header |

---

### 12. 🖼️ Image List / Layer Panel (Sidebar)
- Appears below the upload zone when at least one image is on the page.
- Shows a **thumbnail**, **filename**, and **current dimensions** for each image.
- Click any item to **select** that image and bring it to the front (highest z-index).
- Selected image is highlighted with a cyan glow.
- Scrollable panel with a custom scrollbar.

